 produce an induced\ntransparency-like phenomenon due to the coupling of defect modes and crystal\nsurface states known as Tamm states. The demonstrated active control of coupled\nplasmonic resonators opens previously unexplored avenues for sensitive direct\nand heterodyne THz detection, planar metamaterials, and slow-light devices.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 10 May 2016 18:00:25 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-05-11"}
