al offset from its\ncenter, which is consistent with the local supernova rate. We summarize future\nprospects and ongoing efforts to pin down electromagnetic counterparts of\nbinary black hole mergers as well as neutron star mergers.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 10 May 2016 21:17:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-07-06"}
